speech.p:
asked the Secretary of State for the Home Department (1) what was the cost to Government funds of the survey of homosexuality undertaken at the request of his Department in 1958 by Mr. Richard Hauser; and if he will make a statement;

(2) what precautions his Department takes to ensure that those appointed to residential youth establishments under

his control are not homosexually inclined.

asked the Prime Minister (1) if, in his conversations with President de Gaulle, he discussed the


possibility of constructing a Channel Tunnel;

(2) what reply he gave to President de Gaulle's request, made during their recent conversations, to share nuclear secrets with the United Kingdom.
